<!-- Welcome -->
<section id="welcome">
    <h2><span class="icon">👋</span>Welcome to Week 2</h2>

    <p>In Week 1, you explored workforce development as a system.</p>
    <p><strong>In Week 2, we go deeper.</strong></p>

    <p>This session shifts the focus from <strong>who is in the system</strong> → to <strong>how the system produces outcomes</strong>.</p>

    <ul>
        <li>some individuals advance</li>
        <li>others remain stuck</li>
        <li>many cycle through services without long-term mobility</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
        👉 These outcomes are shaped by how systems are designed.
    </div>

    <h3>Why This Matters</h3>

    <ul>
        <li>access to education and training</li>
        <li>labor market structure and job quality</li>
        <li>employer hiring practices</li>
        <li>availability of supports</li>
        <li>policy and funding decisions</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="callout">
        👉 When systems are misaligned, even strong programs struggle to produce lasting outcomes.
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
        <strong>Week 2 Focus:</strong><br><br>
        Understanding economic mobility as a system outcome — and identifying where systems enable or limit advancement.
    </div>
</section>

